      <div style="font-weight:700;font-size:0.85rem;color:#a0c0f0;margin-bottom:6px;">💙 Delphinium Care — Longmont Specific</div>
      <div style="font-size:0.79rem;line-height:1.6;color:var(--petal);">
        Delphiniums are actually <strong>perfectly suited to Colorado</strong> — they love cool nights and full sun days, which is exactly what Longmont delivers. A few things to know:<br><br>
        • <strong>Staking:</strong> They get tall (3–5ft) and Longmont's wind will knock them over. Stake early — put the stake in now before roots spread.<br>
        • <strong>Water:</strong> Deep watering every 2–3 days. They like consistent moisture but hate soggy roots.<br>
        • <strong>Deadhead</strong> spent spikes down to a side shoot for a second flush of blooms in late summer.<br>
        • <strong>Toxic to pets</strong> — worth noting if Cashew has access to this area.
